{\an8}INTERVIEWER

34
00:03:32,713 --> 00:03:34,841
{\an8}INTERVIEWER

35
00:03:45,977 --> 00:03:47,436
{\an8}Your hobby is playing the piano,

36
00:03:48,229 --> 00:03:49,605
{\an8}yet you played "Chopsticks."

37
00:03:50,523 --> 00:03:52,150
It's my hobby, not my specialty.

38
00:03:52,233 --> 00:03:54,193
I'm not that good, but I enjoy playing.

39
00:03:56,988 --> 00:03:58,197
Can you smile for us?

40
00:04:15,423 --> 00:04:16,424
{\an8}Hey.

41
00:04:19,886 --> 00:04:21,137
{\an8}You really did that?

42
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:23,222
{\an8}Yes. What else was I supposed to do?

43
00:04:23,306 --> 00:04:25,391
{\an8}But still, it was King Hotel.

44
00:04:25,475 --> 00:04:27,685
{\an8}You should've at least
played something by Beethoven.

45
00:04:32,273 --> 00:04:33,399
{\an8}Wonderful.

46
00:04:33,483 --> 00:04:34,650
{\an8}You pass.

47
00:04:34,734 --> 00:04:37,570
{\an8}Thank you, ma'am. I'll work hard.

48
00:04:38,196 --> 00:04:41,407
{\an8}Hey, Beethoven or Mozart.
None of that matters.

49
00:04:41,491 --> 00:04:44,660
They require bachelor's degrees
from mere one-month trainees.

50
00:04:45,244 --> 00:04:46,996
Then why did you go for the interview?

51
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:48,039
Just because.

52
00:04:48,122 --> 00:04:50,458
I wondered how Korea's best hotel
conducted their interviews.

53
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:53,461
If you've satisfied your curiosity,
join me at the duty-free shop.

54
00:04:53,544 --> 00:04:55,963
Don't listen to her.
Be a flight attendant with me.

55
00:04:56,672 --> 00:04:59,217
No, I'm going to work in a hotel.

56
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,801
Come on. Why?

57
00:05:00,885 --> 00:05:02,136
I just like hotels.

58
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:05,139
More than you like me?

59
00:05:05,723 --> 00:05:08,267
Hey, you like nightclubs
more than you like me.

60
00:05:10,436 --> 00:05:11,521
How upsetting.

61
00:05:11,604 --> 00:05:13,147
How could you say that?

62
00:05:13,231 --> 00:05:14,273
It can't be helped.

63
00:05:15,191 --> 00:05:16,275
Let's go clubbing.

64
00:05:17,026 --> 00:05:18,027
Right now?

65
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:19,320
Let's go where?

66
00:05:19,403 --> 00:05:21,656
- Let's go!
- What are you talking about?

67
00:05:22,406 --> 00:05:23,366
Excuse me.

68
00:05:24,075 --> 00:05:25,743
I've been watching you for a while.

69
00:05:25,826 --> 00:05:27,411
Would you care for a drink?

70
00:05:39,298 --> 00:05:40,174
I'm sorry.

71
00:05:40,258 --> 00:05:43,094
We were in the middle
of something important.

72
00:05:44,387 --> 00:05:46,055
You can just give me your number.

73
00:05:47,473 --> 00:05:48,516
Hey.

74
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:54,814
There we go.

75
00:05:56,357 --> 00:05:57,650
I'll get in touch with you.

76
00:06:01,279 --> 00:06:03,531
Hey, why would you
give your number to a stranger?

77
00:06:03,614 --> 00:06:05,992
What do you mean by "stranger"?
We're acquainted now.

78
00:06:06,075 --> 00:06:08,703
Didn't I tell you to start a relationship
after you developed feelings

79
00:06:08,786 --> 00:06:10,079
instead of regretting it later?

80
00:06:10,162 --> 00:06:12,415
Hey, love doesn't happen in stages.

81
00:06:12,498 --> 00:06:14,000
I'm dying to know

82
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:16,252
who you'll get married to
with that mindset.

83
00:06:16,919 --> 00:06:17,878
Are you crazy?

84
00:06:17,962 --> 00:06:20,589
Why would I settle with one person
for the rest of my life?

85
00:06:21,549 --> 00:06:23,467
Even the thought is frightening. Let's go.

86
00:06:23,551 --> 00:06:24,427
Let's go.

87
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:27,680
I'll pass. I'm so tired.

88
00:06:27,763 --> 00:06:29,682
- That's why you go clubbing.
- I mean…

89
00:06:29,765 --> 00:06:33,227
You just got off your flight.
You should get some rest.

90
00:06:33,311 --> 00:06:35,313
No sleep at all is better
than just a few hours.

91
00:06:35,396 --> 00:06:36,230
Grab her.

92
00:06:37,315 --> 00:06:39,984
- I'm not in the mood today.
- Goodness.

93
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:41,402
I'm feeling pumped already.

94
00:07:52,764 --> 00:07:53,806
Who is it?

95
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,603
Hello?

96
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:03,691
Yes, I'm Number 511, Cheon Sa-rang.

97
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:07,654
Sorry?

98
00:08:08,363 --> 00:08:09,447
Really?

99
00:08:11,491 --> 00:08:12,450
I did?

100
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:13,576
But why?

101
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:17,205
No, that's not what I meant.

102
00:08:17,288 --> 00:08:20,083
Okay, thank you.

103
00:08:32,303 --> 00:08:34,097
Why? What's wrong?

104
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:35,139
What's the matter?

105
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:36,307
I passed.

106
00:08:38,977 --> 00:08:41,479
I got an offer from King Hotel!

107
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:46,109
Congratulations, Sa-rang!

108
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:42,975
- Hello?
- <i>You landed in the wrong place.</i>

109
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:46,312
- Sorry?
- <i>It's the building next to you.</i>

110
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:53,069
Over here!

111
00:10:53,736 --> 00:10:55,947
Over here!

112
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:58,699
Over here!

113
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:00,660
Over here!

114
00:11:02,537 --> 00:11:04,914
EPISODE 1

115
00:11:10,128 --> 00:11:12,046
The most important quality of an intern

116
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:14,632
is not how good they are at their job.

117
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:16,134
It's having common sense.

118
00:11:16,843 --> 00:11:19,929
No matter how nimble you are
or how hard you work,

119
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:22,223
it's over for you
if people find you thoughtless.

120
00:11:22,306 --> 00:11:23,141
The end.

121
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:26,144
Consider arriving late
on your first day of work

122
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:28,980
and saying, "I thought it was
the building next door."

123
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:30,773
What ridiculous excuse is that?

124
00:11:30,857 --> 00:11:31,983
What are you…

125
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:34,652
Where did you buy your shoes?

126
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:38,447
I bought them in Milan.

127
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:39,490
Milan?

128
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:43,119
A three-piece suit and shoes from Milan.

129
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:44,954
You could be mistaken for a nobleman.

130
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:46,789
- You should laugh along.
- Yes, sir.

131
00:11:46,873 --> 00:11:49,750
You need to laugh now
if you want to be seen as mindful.

132
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:53,254
All right. Starting now,
I'll teach you what it means to have…

133
00:11:53,921 --> 00:11:55,631
This is fake, isn't it?

134
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:56,716
No.

135
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:58,050
It's authentic?

136
00:11:58,134 --> 00:12:00,845
Look at you. Goodness. Hold on.

137
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,686
How much does your outfit cost?

138
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:09,812
Are you a chaebol?

139
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:11,731
Well…

140
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:15,026
- No.
- See? I knew it.

141
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:15,985
Look at you.

142
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:17,570
He's acting like one.

143
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:20,156
You're on the path of self-destruction.

144
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:22,325
This is what you call being thoughtless.

145
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:23,618
While you're in my charge,

146
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:25,912
don't think of doing anything
and just follow my orders.

147
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,830
- Yes, sir.
- Louder. Got it?

148
00:12:27,914 --> 00:12:29,332
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

149
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:30,499
{\an8}SALES SUPPORT TEAM
INTERN GU WON

150
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:39,884
This is your first internship, right?

151
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:41,093
Don't be late tomorrow.

152
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:42,511
I wasn't late.

153
00:12:43,304 --> 00:12:45,723
If you come to work on the dot,
it means you're late.

154
00:12:45,806 --> 00:12:48,100
Come to work
at least 30 minutes early. Got it?

155
00:12:49,727 --> 00:12:51,979
But why are you speaking so casually?

156
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:53,731
Because we're coworkers.

157
00:12:54,357 --> 00:12:56,859
We have to get through
this unfriendly world together.

158
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:59,570
Don't just sit there.
Uncross your legs and do something.

159
00:12:59,654 --> 00:13:02,073
Do what? There's nothing to do.

160
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:04,825
You still have to act
like you're doing something.

161
00:13:04,909 --> 00:13:08,037
Here. I'll give you a calculator,
so press some buttons.

162
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,330
I said uncross your legs.

163
00:13:09,413 --> 00:13:10,665
And you heard him earlier, right?

164
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:12,792
You shouldn't wear
expensive suits or watches.

165
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,752
Wear something old like mine if you must.

166
00:13:14,835 --> 00:13:16,879
Do I have to? Why?

167
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:20,508
Wearing something more expensive
than your superiors is considered mutiny.

168
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:22,301
You can flaunt your money outside of work.

169
00:13:22,385 --> 00:13:23,678
I never flaunted it.

170
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:25,846
My goodness. You're absolutely clueless.

171
00:13:26,973 --> 00:13:29,433
One would think
you were parachuted into the job.

172
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:31,727
You're right.

173
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:33,437
I parachuted here.

174
00:13:34,188 --> 00:13:35,064
What?

175
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:37,358
I had to rush in from Jeju Island.

176
00:13:38,275 --> 00:13:39,443
Is there something wrong?

177
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:41,362
You're driving me crazy.

178
00:13:44,281 --> 00:13:45,324
Listen carefully.

179
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:47,743
This is my fifth internship.

180
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:49,161
If you keep acting like this,

181
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:53,040
you won't even be able to land a job
as a contract worker. Get it together.

182
00:13:53,124 --> 00:13:55,251
- Interns!
- Yes, sir. No Sang-sik reporting.

183
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:57,336
- Interns.
- Yes, No Sang-sik here.

184
00:13:57,420 --> 00:13:58,504
Why did you come alone?

185
00:13:58,587 --> 00:14:00,089
- Did we only hire one intern?
- No, sir.

186
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:01,799
I thought you were just calling me.

187
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:03,509
Where are you going? Just call him.

188
00:14:03,592 --> 00:14:05,344
- Right.
- What are you doing?

189
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:13,853
What? What is he doing?

190
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:15,730
He needs to sit when he works, you see.

191
00:14:15,813 --> 00:14:17,898
Goodness. He got up.

192
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:19,316
Look at how relaxed he is.

193
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,694
How cool. I thought you were the chairman.

194
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:24,488
It's because this is his first internship.

195
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:25,823
I'll help him out.

196
00:14:25,906 --> 00:14:27,700
- Yes, please help me out too.
- Yes, sir.

197
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:28,826
- To general affairs.
- Yes, sir.

198
00:14:28,909 --> 00:14:30,995
And make three copies of each.

199
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,540
Take your hand out of your pocket.

200
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:37,209
Make copies. Yes, sir. Here.

201
00:14:37,293 --> 00:14:39,003
Go.

202
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:42,006
HOW TO USE A COPIER

203
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:48,721
You're still not done?

204
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:51,724
I didn't know how to use this,
so I was looking it up.

205
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:53,267
How could you not know that?

206
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:55,644
Since I've never used it before.

207
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,271
Are you a young master or what?

208
00:14:57,355 --> 00:14:59,648
Have your servants
been doing these chores for you?

209
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:03,235
Also, this is the scanner. Don't use this.

210
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:05,279
Look. Just press this button.

211
00:15:05,363 --> 00:15:07,156
We have to replace the toner cartridge.

212
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:10,284
- Interns, what are you doing here?
- Yes, sir?

213
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:12,870
It says we need to
replace the toner cartridge.

214
00:15:12,953 --> 00:15:15,664
Gosh, we asked for a new machine ages ago.

215
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:17,750
The machine has a sensor issue.
Just give it a shake.

216
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,168
- Shake it?
- Yes, shake it.

217
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:20,669
Yes, sir.

218
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:23,047
How cute. Are you going to be that gentle?

219
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:25,674
- Shake vigorously.
- What if it explodes?

220
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:27,718
- I said, shake it vigorously.
- Yes, sir.

221
00:15:27,802 --> 00:15:29,261
- That's it. Good job.
- Yes, sir.

222
00:15:29,345 --> 00:15:30,262
- More.
- Yes, sir.

223
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:32,932
- More.
- More.

224
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:36,102
- More.
- More.

225
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:56,497
Darn it. Who messed with the copier?

226
00:15:58,457 --> 00:16:00,709
My goodness. I can't believe you guys.

227
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:02,545
You're driving me insane.

228
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:03,879
- Who was it?
- Darn it.

229
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:07,716
I'm sorry.

230
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,009
I was told to shake it so…

231
00:16:09,093 --> 00:16:11,095
That's not even that expensive.

232
00:16:11,178 --> 00:16:13,389
You could've just gotten a new one.

233
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:15,808
Are we living in the '80s?
Why would you shake that?

234
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:17,643
Well, the thing is…

235
00:16:17,726 --> 00:16:20,855
You have a lot to say
after causing trouble. Just be quiet.

236
00:16:21,772 --> 00:16:22,773
I'm sorry.

237
00:16:22,857 --> 00:16:25,317
Why did they hire a blockhead like you?

238
00:16:26,152 --> 00:16:27,695
- Clean the mess!
- Yes, sir.

239
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:30,156
Why are you sorry?
You didn't do anything wrong.

240
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:32,533
Of course I'm at fault.

241
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:34,618
- It's all my fault. Why…
- How so?

242
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,246
Hey.

243
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:39,415
What did you just say?

244
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:42,334
I said it wasn't
Intern No Sang-sik's fault.

245
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:43,294
Why not?

246
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:46,464
He just followed orders
because he was told to.

247
00:16:46,547 --> 00:16:48,340
If it resulted in a negative outcome,

248
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:51,385
isn't the person
who gave the order at fault?

249
00:16:52,303 --> 00:16:53,471
Stop it.

250
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:55,681
- What?
- I believe it's not right

251
00:16:55,764 --> 00:16:58,100
to blame your juniors
without determining the cause.

252
00:16:58,184 --> 00:17:00,269
Also, this only happened

253
00:17:00,352 --> 00:17:02,980
because the copier was not replaced
when it should've been.

254
00:17:04,565 --> 00:17:06,025
So the company is most at fault.

255
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:08,360
How dare an intern criticize the company?

256
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:11,197
Even a mere intern
can tell right from wrong.

257
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,157
- Darn you.
- I'm sorry.

258
00:17:13,782 --> 00:17:16,368
This punk has no sense in him.

259
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:19,580
Clean up this mess at once and get lost.

260
00:17:19,663 --> 00:17:21,665
And don't come to work starting tomorrow.

