00:17:22,249 --> 00:17:23,751
No, I have to come to work.

262
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:24,877
- I'm sorry.
- Okay.

263
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:27,213
- I'll do that.
- What?

264
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:28,255
You'll what?

265
00:17:28,339 --> 00:17:29,423
Don't move! Where are you going?

266
00:17:30,758 --> 00:17:32,968
- You said to clean up the mess.
- Yes, right here.

267
00:17:35,513 --> 00:17:36,555
Hello, it's me.

268
00:17:37,223 --> 00:17:39,808
Can you send some cleaners
to the sales support team?

269
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:42,144
Yes.

270
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:44,230
The copier also needs to be replaced.

271
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:45,314
All right.

272
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:48,984
- He said he'll send them.
- Who?

273
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:50,528
The cleaners.

274
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:51,529
Who said that?

275
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:53,489
- Director Choi.
- Director Choi?

276
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:54,698
By Director Choi…

277
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:58,285
The only Director Choi here

278
00:17:58,369 --> 00:18:02,248
is the one who works
in the chairman's secretary's office.

279
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:03,999
That's right.

280
00:18:05,376 --> 00:18:08,128
If you don't mind me asking, who are you?

281
00:18:11,632 --> 00:18:12,883
I'm an intern,

282
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:15,302
and my name is Gu Won.

283
00:18:17,596 --> 00:18:19,431
Gu Won?

284
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:22,059
Then are you Chairman Gu Il-hun's…

285
00:18:23,394 --> 00:18:24,353
That's right.

286
00:18:26,021 --> 00:18:27,022
Goodness.

287
00:18:27,523 --> 00:18:30,150
Goodness, you look amazing in this suit.

288
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:31,652
Then I guess

289
00:18:31,735 --> 00:18:34,363
I won't come to work
starting tomorrow as you ordered.

290
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:36,490
No, ignore what I said. I'm sorry.

291
00:18:36,574 --> 00:18:38,450
Don't apologize. I'm a mere intern.

292
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:40,411
I just need to do as I'm told.

293
00:18:41,704 --> 00:18:43,539
Excuse me, Mr. Choi.

294
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:45,165
Choi Tae-man at your service.

295
00:18:45,249 --> 00:18:46,625
Thanks to you,

296
00:18:47,459 --> 00:18:49,753
I now have a good grasp of
what thoughtlessness is.

297
00:18:49,837 --> 00:18:51,005
I'll be born again.

298
00:18:51,547 --> 00:18:52,923
Hello, Mr. Choi.

299
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:54,341
What's wrong with the copier?

300
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,802
Are you hurt anywhere?

301
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:59,930
I'm fine. Please just handle the mess.

302
00:19:00,014 --> 00:19:00,973
Hold on.

303
00:19:01,724 --> 00:19:03,809
I was told to
manage your attendance strictly.

304
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:06,979
If you leave now,
the chairman will be furious.

305
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:08,314
I just…

306
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:10,649
got fired.

307
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:12,818
- No, it was a joke.
- I'm leaving.

308
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:15,696
Won.

309
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:17,573
You come over here.

310
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:18,741
- It's all your fault!
- I'm sorry.

311
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:20,909
- Why did you have to shake that?
- I'm sorry.

312
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:22,578
I can't get fired though.

313
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:24,121
- I need to stay here.
- I can't believe this.

314
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:27,207
I didn't know
that shaking the cartridge would…

315
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:29,084
You're back, sir.

316
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,211
Do you want to go with me?

317
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:35,299
- Me?
- As coworkers,

318
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:37,384
we need to get through
this unfriendly world together.

319
00:19:38,052 --> 00:19:40,429
You said staying here won't even
guarantee you a contract position.

320
00:19:40,512 --> 00:19:43,307
Come with me
and you'll get a full-time position.

321
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:52,274
I will serve you
with my utmost sincerity, sir.

322
00:19:55,486 --> 00:19:57,029
- Do I need to clean this?
- I'll take care of it.

323
00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:58,030
- Okay, then.
- Sure.

324
00:19:58,113 --> 00:19:59,782
- Here you go.
- You may give it to me.

325
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:01,700
- I hope you'll be born again.
- Thank you.

326
00:20:01,784 --> 00:20:03,827
Let's go, sir.

327
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:06,705
Coming through. Please make way.

328
00:20:06,789 --> 00:20:09,124
- Gosh, why did you…
- <i>Are you in your right mind?!</i>

329
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:11,752
I told you to learn from the bottom up.

330
00:20:11,835 --> 00:20:13,212
And you left on the first day?

331
00:20:13,921 --> 00:20:16,340
I didn't choose to leave.
I got kicked out.

332
00:20:16,423 --> 00:20:18,842
Either way, I already told you
that I'm not cut out for this.

333
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:20,803
I'll go back to the UK.

334
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:22,262
- What will you do there?
- Dad.

335
00:20:22,346 --> 00:20:23,639
That's enough.

336
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:27,142
He can start slowly after studying more.

337
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:29,645
And I know it's good
to start from the bottom,

338
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,397
but an intern was too much.

339
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:33,607
Why can't you be
half as good as your sister?

340
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,776
Who does he take after?

341
00:20:35,859 --> 00:20:38,487
Don't be too harsh on him.
I'll try talking to him.

342
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:41,782
Can we talk?

343
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:46,704
Go to the hotel.

344
00:20:46,787 --> 00:20:48,205
It's a hassle.

345
00:20:48,872 --> 00:20:50,124
I'll stay here tonight.

346
00:20:51,542 --> 00:20:52,835
Who are you to stay here?

347
00:20:57,005 --> 00:20:58,132
Don't be mistaken.

348
00:20:58,215 --> 00:20:59,633
This isn't your house.

349
00:21:03,721 --> 00:21:04,805
You're right.

350
00:21:04,888 --> 00:21:06,640
I forgot for a second.

351
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:09,309
Stay at the hotel
and fly out as soon as possible.

352
00:21:09,893 --> 00:21:11,395
Whatever you choose to do,

353
00:21:11,478 --> 00:21:13,021
I'll support you financially.

354
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:16,650
So don't even think about
lurking around the house or the company.

355
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:24,074
You know,

356
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:26,076
I'm loaded too.

357
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:31,206
But thanks for looking after me.

358
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:34,626
You almost moved me for a second.

359
00:21:49,808 --> 00:21:50,726
Where's Won?

360
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:52,978
He said he'd stay at the hotel
for the time being.

361
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:55,606
I insisted that he should at least eat.

362
00:21:58,150 --> 00:21:59,151
That imbecile.

363
00:21:59,777 --> 00:22:02,404
That wasn't even an earful,
but he ran away without eating.

364
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:04,031
He still has a long way to go.

365
00:22:04,114 --> 00:22:06,825
If you keep tugging,
he'll only run farther away.

366
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:09,787
Letting him be
might be a good option for now.

367
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:12,539
All right.

368
00:22:13,248 --> 00:22:16,293
Make sure you don't
give him a hard time either.

369
00:24:14,828 --> 00:24:16,204
The guest is what?

370
00:24:16,288 --> 00:24:17,831
- The guest is king.
- The guest is king.

371
00:24:17,914 --> 00:24:20,167
That's right. The guest is king.

372
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:21,168
Why?

373
00:24:21,251 --> 00:24:23,754
Because guests pay
service charges at hotels.

374
00:24:23,837 --> 00:24:27,090
Because of that, it is our duty
to treat our guests like the king,

375
00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:30,218
and it gives them the right
to be treated like one as well.

376
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:32,387
We aim to provide the guests
with satisfactory service

377
00:24:32,471 --> 00:24:34,765
as well as to move their hearts.

378
00:24:34,848 --> 00:24:38,310
We have to forget about our emotions
for the sake of our guests.

379
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:41,313
If you feel you're not up to it,
you may leave now.

380
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:45,484
No one?

381
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:47,444
Are you all ready to serve the king?

382
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:48,403
- Yes.
- Yes.

383
00:24:48,487 --> 00:24:50,739
Quality customer service
starts with a smile.

384
00:24:50,822 --> 00:24:53,909
This is the high-end smile
that only King Hotel offers.

385
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:55,702
Hermès!

386
00:24:55,786 --> 00:24:57,162
- Hermès!
- Hermès!

387
00:24:57,245 --> 00:25:00,624
A smile is the greatest sword and shield.

388
00:25:00,707 --> 00:25:03,085
Beautifully, Hermès!

389
00:25:03,669 --> 00:25:05,087
- Hermès!
- Hermès!

390
00:25:11,718 --> 00:25:13,220
Hello, Manager Kim.

391
00:25:13,303 --> 00:25:14,763
What's wrong with the floor?

392
00:25:14,846 --> 00:25:16,014
We just cleaned it.

393
00:25:16,098 --> 00:25:18,433
Clean it again and again
until it's sparkling clean.

394
00:25:19,059 --> 00:25:20,352
She's a trainee.

395
00:25:20,435 --> 00:25:22,604
Hello, I'm Cheon Sa-rang.

396
00:25:22,688 --> 00:25:23,814
I'll take a look around.

397
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:26,233
- Teach her from A to Z.
- Yes, ma'am.

398
00:25:32,781 --> 00:25:34,783
You're uselessly pretty
for a one-month trainee.

399
00:25:35,492 --> 00:25:38,161
- Pardon?
- You'll be gone in a month.

400
00:25:38,245 --> 00:25:39,538
Go and wipe the butt sweat.

401
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:41,331
"Butt sweat"?

402
00:25:41,915 --> 00:25:43,166
If you go over there,

403
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:46,128
you'll see the beautiful butt sweat
left by our guests.

404
00:25:46,211 --> 00:25:48,088
You'll be in charge of that for a month,

405
00:25:48,171 --> 00:25:50,757
so don't miss a single drop
and wipe until it's sparkling clean.

406
00:25:51,341 --> 00:25:52,217
Yes, ma'am.

407
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:03,478
Hey you.

408
00:26:04,146 --> 00:26:05,063
Hermès!

409
00:26:05,981 --> 00:26:06,898
Hermès!

410
00:26:17,701 --> 00:26:19,494
Hermès.

411
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,246
Hermès.

412
00:26:24,291 --> 00:26:26,918
Cotton swabs and cotton pads
should be filled to 90%.

413
00:26:27,002 --> 00:26:28,795
It's difficult to take one out at 100%.

414
00:26:28,879 --> 00:26:31,256
Anything under 90%
makes it look like we don't care.

415
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:33,300
Yes, ma'am.

416
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:36,344
Why are you so smiley?

417
00:26:36,428 --> 00:26:39,264
I was taught to maintain
my Hermès smile while working.

418
00:26:39,347 --> 00:26:40,807
That applies to concierges.

419
00:26:40,891 --> 00:26:42,476
We still work in the hotel.

420
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:44,978
The true hotel working experience
starts in the lobby.

421
00:26:45,061 --> 00:26:47,481
We wear sportswear
while they wear uniforms.

422
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:51,359
Plus, you're only here for a month.
You don't need to get used to Hermès.

423
00:26:52,277 --> 00:26:54,404
I should still try my best while I'm here.

424
00:26:54,488 --> 00:26:55,530
Try all you want.

425
00:26:55,614 --> 00:26:58,575
No matter what happens,
you won't be able to go near the lobby.

426
00:26:58,658 --> 00:27:01,745
Even I've been stuck here for five years.

427
00:27:01,828 --> 00:27:03,663
At least you're a full-time worker.

428
00:27:06,249 --> 00:27:07,292
Well…

429
00:27:08,084 --> 00:27:09,836
I'm better than you in every aspect.

430
00:27:10,629 --> 00:27:14,466
If you're done here, go out and wipe
until everything's sparkling clean.

431
00:27:14,549 --> 00:27:17,260
Okay. I'll wipe
until everything's sparkling clean.

432
00:27:20,388 --> 00:27:23,350
Let's get up early tomorrow
so we can eat something before our flight.

433
00:27:23,433 --> 00:27:26,561
Pyeong-hwa, look up some famous places
nearby and make a reservation.

434
00:27:26,645 --> 00:27:28,396
We have the hotel breakfast reserved.

435
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,606
I asked for a famous restaurant.

436
00:27:29,689 --> 00:27:31,399
Find a rare restaurant with food

437
00:27:31,483 --> 00:27:32,818
that is unique to this place.

438
00:27:32,901 --> 00:27:36,321
Yes, ma'am.
I will look for a rare restaurant.

439
00:27:36,404 --> 00:27:37,781
We're checked in.

440
00:27:39,991 --> 00:27:41,660
Who wants to share a room with me?

441
00:27:45,747 --> 00:27:46,998
Then should I choose?

442
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:52,963
<i>Who will share a room with me?</i>

443
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:58,218
<i>I wonder who it will be</i>

444
00:27:58,885 --> 00:28:00,720
<i>Eeny, meeny, miny…</i>

445
00:28:03,557 --> 00:28:04,558
<i>moe!</i>

446
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:06,226
You win!

447
00:28:13,942 --> 00:28:14,985
Be done in ten minutes.

448
00:28:15,068 --> 00:28:16,736
Don't use the restroom while I'm sleeping.

449
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:18,238
- Yes, ma'am.
- Unplug all the TV

450
00:28:18,321 --> 00:28:19,364
and fridge cables.

451
00:28:19,447 --> 00:28:21,408
I can't sleep if it's noisy. Understood?

452
00:28:21,992 --> 00:28:23,201
Yes, ma'am. I…

453
00:28:25,745 --> 00:28:28,874
RARE RESTAURANTS IN JEJU ISLAND

454
00:28:31,042 --> 00:28:33,086
Didn't I tell you that I'm sensitive?

455
00:28:33,169 --> 00:28:35,088
I could sense the electromagnetic waves.

456
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:36,882
I'm sorry.

457
00:28:36,965 --> 00:28:39,175
- Turn off your phone.
- I put it on silent.

458
00:28:39,259 --> 00:28:40,844
I can sense that too.

459
00:29:09,623 --> 00:29:12,292
Thank you. Please come again next time.

460
00:29:14,044 --> 00:29:15,712
- Da-eul.
- Yes?

461
00:29:15,795 --> 00:29:18,173
The manager said
she doesn't like the cafeteria menu.

462
00:29:18,256 --> 00:29:20,175
She wants some <i>gimbap</i> to eat in the back.

463
00:29:20,759 --> 00:29:22,260
All right. I'll be right back.

464
00:29:26,306 --> 00:29:28,183
Sorry. Coming through.

465
00:29:29,768 --> 00:29:31,311
One tuna, two beef,

466
00:29:31,394 --> 00:29:33,438
and one kimchi rice ball to go.

467
00:29:33,521 --> 00:29:35,232
Okay, I got your order.

468
00:29:35,315 --> 00:29:39,236
I'm really sorry, but in the tuna <i>gimbap</i>,
could you please reduce the rice,

469
00:29:39,319 --> 00:29:40,987
add a lot of tuna and mayonnaise,

470
00:29:41,071 --> 00:29:42,822
and take out the spinach?

471
00:29:43,782 --> 00:29:45,075
Sure.

472
00:29:46,243 --> 00:29:49,579
I'm really sorry again,
but for one of the beef <i>gimbap</i>,

473
00:29:49,663 --> 00:29:52,415
can you leave out
the sesame oil and carrots?

474
00:29:53,250 --> 00:29:54,417
Why don't you make it yourself?

475
00:29:54,501 --> 00:29:57,254
I'm sorry. My seniors are picky eaters.

476
00:29:57,337 --> 00:29:59,506
Just for today. I can't cater to
your needs when I'm busy.

477
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:00,882
Thank you so much.

478
00:30:01,675 --> 00:30:03,134
I'm really sorry again…

479
00:30:03,218 --> 00:30:05,095
- What now?
- Along with the other requests,

480
00:30:05,178 --> 00:30:07,180
for the other beef <i>gimbap</i>,
can you take out the eggs

481
00:30:07,264 --> 00:30:10,475
and apply the right amount of sesame oil
to make it give off a slight scent?

482
00:30:10,558 --> 00:30:12,852
- Get out. I'm done with you.
- I'm sorry.

483
00:30:12,936 --> 00:30:14,187
Please help me out.

484
00:30:14,271 --> 00:30:16,231
- I need to buy the <i>gimbap</i>.
- Get out!

485
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:17,440
I'll make them.

486
00:30:17,524 --> 00:30:20,068
At least allow me to make them. Please.

487
00:30:20,819 --> 00:30:22,862
Excuse me. Sorry.

488
00:30:28,076 --> 00:30:29,786
I'm back. I'll get everything ready.

489
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:31,955
The manager went to the cafeteria.

490
00:30:32,038 --> 00:30:33,164
Sorry?

491
00:30:33,915 --> 00:30:34,874
What about these?

492
00:30:35,917 --> 00:30:38,837
Didn't you hear me? She wants
the pork cutlet from the cafeteria.

493
00:30:40,922 --> 00:30:41,923
Let's go.

494
00:30:56,313 --> 00:30:57,522
Where's the water?

495
00:31:00,942 --> 00:31:01,985
- Hello.
- Hello.

496
00:31:02,068 --> 00:31:03,570
- This is Alanga.
- This is King Hotel.

497
00:31:04,154 --> 00:31:05,363
- Over there.
- Yes, ma'am.

498
00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:13,288
Apologizing doesn't solve the problem!

499
00:31:14,289 --> 00:31:16,374
Welcome. May I check your boarding pass?

500
00:31:18,793 --> 00:31:19,836
Coming!

501
00:32:03,588 --> 00:32:04,714
I can't believe my eyes.

502
00:32:06,299 --> 00:32:07,842
Sir, I'm here.

503
00:32:10,678 --> 00:32:11,763
Next.

504
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:17,644
Are you purchasing your clothes here?

505
00:32:18,436 --> 00:32:20,188
Why would I bother shopping in person?

506
00:32:21,106 --> 00:32:23,650
The comfort of the rich is beautiful.

507
00:32:25,026 --> 00:32:28,071
What do you think of this?
There are only three in the nation.

508
00:32:29,614 --> 00:32:30,490
Give me all three.

509
00:32:30,573 --> 00:32:33,368
I'm sorry, but one has already been sold.

510
00:32:33,451 --> 00:32:35,078
Then give me the remaining two.

511
00:32:35,787 --> 00:32:36,788
I'm okay.

512
00:32:37,372 --> 00:32:39,124
Matching shirts seems a bit too much.

513
00:32:39,207 --> 00:32:40,834
I appreciate your gesture though.

514
00:32:40,917 --> 00:32:41,793
Matching shirts?

515
00:32:41,876 --> 00:32:42,794
Why would I?

516
00:32:43,378 --> 00:32:44,712
Weren't you going to give one to me?

517
00:32:44,796 --> 00:32:45,880
