00:53:00,302 --> 00:53:02,387
You guys can practice smiling.

776
00:53:02,971 --> 00:53:04,097
Hermès!

777
00:53:04,181 --> 00:53:05,349
- Hermès!
- Hermès!

778
00:53:14,983 --> 00:53:16,193
{\an8}How may I help you, ma'am?

779
00:53:16,777 --> 00:53:18,528
{\an8}I'm in charge of the reception desk
at the moment.

780
00:53:18,612 --> 00:53:20,781
{\an8}Are you the one that made
my wake-up call this morning?

781
00:53:20,864 --> 00:53:23,492
{\an8}Yes, I did. At the time you requested.

782
00:53:23,575 --> 00:53:25,702
{\an8}So, you knew who I am?

783
00:53:26,203 --> 00:53:29,122
{\an8}How could any music lover right now
recognize you?

784
00:53:30,207 --> 00:53:32,876
{\an8}It's a great honor to have you stay
at our hotel.

785
00:53:40,467 --> 00:53:44,763
{\an8}<i>I've had countless wake-up calls
from hotels all around the world.</i>

786
00:53:54,147 --> 00:53:56,149
{\an8}<i>But it was the first time</i>

787
00:53:56,233 --> 00:53:59,403
{\an8}<i>I woke up hearing the aria that I sang.</i>

788
00:53:59,486 --> 00:54:02,989
{\an8}<i>It's been a few years
since I left the stage.</i>

789
00:54:03,073 --> 00:54:07,244
{\an8}<i>But it seemed as if
I'd become a prima donna again.</i>

790
00:54:07,327 --> 00:54:08,453
{\an8}<i>Thank you, dear,</i>

791
00:54:08,537 --> 00:54:10,664
{\an8}for taking me back to days of my youth.

792
00:54:11,748 --> 00:54:14,709
{\an8}Thank you for remembering me
after all these years.

793
00:54:15,544 --> 00:54:18,713
{\an8}Now it's my turn to keep you
in my memory, Ms...

794
00:54:20,465 --> 00:54:21,591
{\an8}Sa-rang.

795
00:54:58,962 --> 00:55:01,882
How does it feel to come back
to Korea after a while?

796
00:55:02,716 --> 00:55:03,675
It's the same.

797
00:55:04,301 --> 00:55:06,344
Don't think of leaving again.

798
00:55:06,428 --> 00:55:07,596
Start working.

799
00:55:07,679 --> 00:55:10,724
Hotel, Air, or Distribution?
Which do you prefer?

800
00:55:10,807 --> 00:55:13,185
He's just visiting.
You're getting ahead of yourself.

801
00:55:13,894 --> 00:55:15,312
He's not done with his studies either.

802
00:55:15,395 --> 00:55:17,606
It won't be late
even if he takes his time.

803
00:55:17,689 --> 00:55:18,899
Seven years was more than enough.

804
00:55:19,524 --> 00:55:21,735
Since we're on the topic,
move back to Korea.

805
00:55:24,738 --> 00:55:25,739
I'll start working.

806
00:55:26,865 --> 00:55:27,866
What?

807
00:55:27,949 --> 00:55:30,368
But I want to work at the hotel.

808
00:55:32,537 --> 00:55:33,663
What's your reason?

809
00:55:34,372 --> 00:55:35,457
I like hotels.

810
00:55:37,542 --> 00:55:38,460
All right.

811
00:55:38,543 --> 00:55:39,503
Go ahead.

812
00:55:40,962 --> 00:55:42,422
Okay. Let's have a drink.

813
00:55:42,506 --> 00:55:46,092
I'm delighted to see
our family gathered like this.

814
00:55:47,302 --> 00:55:49,638
You probably can't even imagine

815
00:55:50,180 --> 00:55:52,098
how long I've waited for this day to come.

816
00:55:52,182 --> 00:55:55,310
Won, you'll need to climb up the ladder
by competing with your sister.

817
00:55:55,393 --> 00:55:56,603
What do you mean?

818
00:55:57,604 --> 00:56:00,106
Won is just now starting out.
I should help him.

819
00:56:00,190 --> 00:56:03,318
Both providing and receiving help
reflect competence.

820
00:56:03,401 --> 00:56:05,862
I'm only going to consider
your competence from now on.

821
00:56:05,946 --> 00:56:08,907
Either one of you
could become my successor,

822
00:56:08,990 --> 00:56:10,367
or it could be neither of you.

823
00:56:10,450 --> 00:56:12,994
I know. That's your management philosophy.

824
00:56:14,538 --> 00:56:15,664
Also,

825
00:56:15,747 --> 00:56:17,999
live here with us
instead of staying at the hotel.

826
00:56:18,917 --> 00:56:20,210
It's more comfortable there.

827
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:22,546
Won is all grown up now.

828
00:56:23,129 --> 00:56:24,464
Let him do as he pleases.

829
00:56:25,882 --> 00:56:27,801
I'm not going to repeat myself.

830
00:56:27,884 --> 00:56:29,761
Come back home
before your mom's memorial service.

831
00:56:31,596 --> 00:56:32,597
Which mom do you mean?

832
00:56:37,102 --> 00:56:38,728
I don't even know

833
00:56:39,396 --> 00:56:42,482
what my mom looks like
or if she's even alive or not.

834
00:56:52,659 --> 00:56:54,869
Stop with the nonsense.

835
00:56:55,453 --> 00:56:57,372
Just move in if I tell you to.

836
00:57:08,258 --> 00:57:10,135
You take after your mom.

837
00:57:11,344 --> 00:57:13,263
You're reckless just like her.

838
00:57:29,821 --> 00:57:31,281
I'll be fine on my own. Go home.

839
00:57:39,039 --> 00:57:41,499
Let me join you. The rain feels nice.

840
00:57:41,583 --> 00:57:43,752
- Don't follow me.
- Whatever.

841
00:57:43,835 --> 00:57:45,837
I know you don't have a friend
to drink with.

842
00:57:46,713 --> 00:57:48,340
I like how you're smart-mouthed.

843
00:57:48,423 --> 00:57:50,467
- True.
- And how you don't force a laugh.

844
00:57:50,550 --> 00:57:51,843
I do though.

845
00:57:57,933 --> 00:58:00,060
What will the starting rank be by the way?

846
00:58:00,560 --> 00:58:03,104
I don't know. It doesn't matter.

847
00:58:03,688 --> 00:58:04,981
What do you mean?

848
00:58:05,065 --> 00:58:06,358
I'm asking for myself.

849
00:58:06,441 --> 00:58:08,234
You got the wrong idea.

850
00:58:08,318 --> 00:58:10,153
I need some authority to protect you.

851
00:58:10,236 --> 00:58:12,948
Who's going to deal
with your toxic personality? I will.

852
00:58:13,031 --> 00:58:14,157
Let me be bold.

853
00:58:15,283 --> 00:58:16,743
Department manager, please.

854
00:58:17,869 --> 00:58:19,162
I went too far, didn't I?

855
00:58:19,245 --> 00:58:20,080
Senior manager?

856
00:58:28,546 --> 00:58:30,590
Take the car and go home.

857
00:58:31,174 --> 00:58:33,677
I'll find my way to the hotel.
Don't follow me.

858
00:58:34,260 --> 00:58:35,720
No, I'm going with you.

859
00:58:36,513 --> 00:58:37,639
I should.

860
00:58:38,640 --> 00:58:40,266
Gosh, the weather

861
00:58:41,059 --> 00:58:43,228
is perfect for me to become a manager.

862
00:58:43,311 --> 00:58:44,729
What kind of weather is that?

863
00:58:45,230 --> 00:58:46,815
Please make me a manager.

864
00:58:46,898 --> 00:58:48,483
- Let go.
- Please.

865
00:58:48,566 --> 00:58:50,443
My goodness!

866
00:58:50,527 --> 00:58:52,153
- Please.
- Why is it raining so hard?

867
00:58:52,237 --> 00:58:53,363
- I know, right?
- Darn it.

868
00:58:54,155 --> 00:58:55,949
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

869
00:59:02,455 --> 00:59:03,665
That's refreshing.

870
00:59:03,748 --> 00:59:05,417
This place has good beer.

871
00:59:05,500 --> 00:59:07,627
Hey, this place
is very popular these days.

872
00:59:07,711 --> 00:59:09,337
There's a line on the weekends.

873
00:59:11,047 --> 00:59:12,298
What's wrong? Are you okay?

874
00:59:12,882 --> 00:59:13,967
My stomach hurts for some reason.

875
00:59:14,050 --> 00:59:15,051
Are you stressed?

876
00:59:15,135 --> 00:59:17,053
This usually happens when you're stressed.

877
00:59:17,137 --> 00:59:19,431
It's obviously because of Gong Yu-nam.

878
00:59:19,514 --> 00:59:20,974
Who's that?

879
00:59:21,933 --> 00:59:23,935
Your boyfriend?

880
00:59:24,019 --> 00:59:26,813
Right. You have a boyfriend.

881
00:59:26,896 --> 00:59:28,565
I totally forgot.

882
00:59:29,065 --> 00:59:30,483
That's enough.

883
00:59:30,567 --> 00:59:32,152
Isn't it about time you broke up with him?

884
00:59:32,235 --> 00:59:33,695
I guess he didn't cross the line yet.

885
00:59:33,778 --> 00:59:36,156
She's so lenient
when it comes to her boyfriend.

886
00:59:36,239 --> 00:59:38,658
I'm more lenient with you guys.
Couldn't you tell?

887
00:59:38,742 --> 00:59:42,328
Hey, holding a hot cup of tea

888
00:59:42,412 --> 00:59:46,207
and saying, "It's hot,"
will only burn your hands.

889
00:59:46,833 --> 00:59:48,835
Don't bottle everything up.
Get it off your chest.

890
00:59:52,297 --> 00:59:53,131
Mom! Aunties!

891
00:59:56,968 --> 00:59:59,596
If you drink here,
you'll destroy my reputation.

892
00:59:59,679 --> 01:00:01,014
I worked so hard to build it.

893
01:00:01,097 --> 01:00:02,599
All right, we'll stop drinking.

894
01:00:02,682 --> 01:00:04,809
Go and play, my daughter.

895
01:00:09,898 --> 01:00:12,192
Your daughter is scarier than you.

896
01:00:12,275 --> 01:00:15,361
I know, right? I'm too scared to drink.

897
01:00:16,571 --> 01:00:19,783
I want to dance
under the lights all night long

898
01:00:20,366 --> 01:00:22,327
holding a bottle of beer.

899
01:00:22,911 --> 01:00:25,955
That sounds great, and it really was.

900
01:00:26,873 --> 01:00:30,168
But I forgot how to dance, so I doubt
I'll have as much fun as I used to.

901
01:00:30,251 --> 01:00:33,088
I don't even remember
what a nightclub looks like.

902
01:01:11,876 --> 01:01:13,086
Gosh, my blood pressure.

903
01:01:39,571 --> 01:01:41,239
Do you need to wear a vest?

904
01:01:41,322 --> 01:01:42,574
It seems like a hassle.

905
01:01:43,449 --> 01:01:46,661
This is how you should wear a suit.

906
01:01:46,744 --> 01:01:47,662
As expected,

907
01:01:47,745 --> 01:01:48,913
you have a classic style.

908
01:01:51,082 --> 01:01:52,584
When are you going to fix this?

909
01:01:53,209 --> 01:01:54,460
Should I get it fixed?

910
01:01:57,547 --> 01:01:58,548
It's okay.

911
01:02:02,927 --> 01:02:04,554
You look amazing today.

912
01:02:10,602 --> 01:02:12,145
It's finally our first day.

913
01:02:12,228 --> 01:02:14,480
Let's start the day with a smile,
Head Manager Gu.

914
01:02:14,564 --> 01:02:16,065
That's what I hate the most.

915
01:02:16,149 --> 01:02:17,483
Faking, putting up a front…

916
01:02:17,567 --> 01:02:18,401
Faking a smile.

917
01:02:19,319 --> 01:02:21,988
I was just saying
that you shouldn't feel too stressed

918
01:02:22,071 --> 01:02:24,324
since all of this will be yours one day.

919
01:02:24,407 --> 01:02:26,993
Maybe it's time for you to lose your job
seeing how you're bossing me around.

920
01:02:28,328 --> 01:02:29,996
No one else would stick around you.

921
01:02:30,079 --> 01:02:32,123
You should be grateful to me.

922
01:02:32,832 --> 01:02:34,167
You're consistently impudent.

923
01:02:34,250 --> 01:02:35,335
True.

924
01:02:35,835 --> 01:02:38,630
If it wasn't for my impudence,
I would've run away ages ago.

925
01:02:38,713 --> 01:02:40,506
Who else would stay by your side?

926
01:02:44,052 --> 01:02:45,762
- My phone.
- You may head inside.

927
01:02:45,845 --> 01:02:47,680
I'll tell them to bring it.

928
01:02:52,185 --> 01:02:54,187
Congratulations on your first day of work.

929
01:03:02,987 --> 01:03:03,905
The papers.

930
01:03:04,697 --> 01:03:05,573
Mr. No.

931
01:03:07,242 --> 01:03:08,243
Mr. No?

932
01:03:14,457 --> 01:03:16,668
Yes.

933
01:03:17,377 --> 01:03:19,587
All right. We'll bring it
to you right away.

934
01:03:19,671 --> 01:03:22,257
Excuse me, Ms. Kim.
I need to use the restroom.

935
01:03:22,340 --> 01:03:24,717
Head straight to the suite, find a phone,

936
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:26,219
and take it to Ms. Gu's office.

937
01:03:26,302 --> 01:03:28,137
Wait, I'm sorry,

938
01:03:28,805 --> 01:03:30,265
but I have a really bad stomachache.

939
01:03:30,348 --> 01:03:31,849
To the point of crapping on the way?

940
01:03:32,934 --> 01:03:34,560
- Yes.
- In that case,

941
01:03:35,395 --> 01:03:36,896
finish the errand quickly and then go.

942
01:03:37,480 --> 01:03:39,357
But this is urgent.

943
01:03:39,440 --> 01:03:41,484
Exactly. Hurry up and hop to it.

944
01:03:43,528 --> 01:03:44,529
Yes, ma'am.

945
01:05:12,617 --> 01:05:13,785
My phone…

946
01:05:15,495 --> 01:05:16,788
I almost died.

947
01:05:19,749 --> 01:05:20,875
What is this?

948
01:05:26,631 --> 01:05:28,549
The bathroom is bigger than my house.

949
01:05:28,633 --> 01:05:30,885
He only took my phone.

950
01:05:32,387 --> 01:05:33,596
This is so cool.

951
01:06:19,183 --> 01:06:22,186
KING THE LAND

952
01:06:54,260 --> 01:06:57,180
{\an8}<i>Please welcome Head Manager Gu Won
with a big round of applause.</i>

953
01:07:00,391 --> 01:07:01,225
{\an8}We…

954
01:07:01,976 --> 01:07:03,102
{\an8}<i>meet again.</i>

955
01:07:03,186 --> 01:07:05,438
{\an8}Welcome, Head Manager Gu!

956
01:07:06,939 --> 01:07:08,691
{\an8}We made eye contact again!

957
01:07:09,609 --> 01:07:11,944
{\an8}I warned you
to never let me see you again.

958
01:07:12,028 --> 01:07:14,155
{\an8}I'll do my best to avoid you from now on.

959
01:07:15,698 --> 01:07:17,450
{\an8}You said you'd do your best to avoid me.

960
01:07:18,576 --> 01:07:20,453
{\an8}<i>Even over my dead body,</i>

961
01:07:21,078 --> 01:07:23,414
{\an8}you are most definitely not my type.

962
